    text: "Chapter 0 ‚Äì Cinematic Cosmic Genesis"
  - line: 5
    type: narration
    text: "Year 0 BH ‚Äì Year 3500 BH"
  - line: 7
    type: narration
    text: "Before the First Coming, the heavens were whole."
  - line: 8
    type: narration
    text: "In the cold expanse beyond the Dragon Nebula, two ancient worlds moved in silent harmony‚ÄîMars, veined with rivers and volcanic light, and Tiamat, vast and blue, its oceans alive with creatures born of vrill and starlight."
  - line: 9
    type: narration
    text: "Upon Tiamat, the Aeon Keepers shaped the flow of creation."
  - line: 10
    type: narration
    text: "Their luminous kin, the Nehereti, danced between thought and matter, guardians of balance, sculptors of harmony."
  - line: 12
    type: narration
    text: "From mountain to sea, their civilization was a fusion of grace and endurance‚Äîstonework carved into cliffs, tree-cities grown from living wood."
  - line: 13
    type: narration
    text: "In the stillness above it all, a lone Nehereti meditated atop a mist-crowned peak, its form half-light, half-dream."
  - line: 14
    type: narration
    text: "It listened to the rhythm of the planet‚Äôs pulse‚Äîand heard it falter."
  - line: 16
    type: narration
    text: "A tremor rippled through the cosmos."
  - line: 17
    type: narration
    text: "A red star flared in the distance, expanding into a furious sun."
  - line: 18
    type: narration
    text: "Marduk, the wandering god-planet, tore across the void, its wake glowing like molten blood."
  - line: 19
    type: narration
    text: "When it struck, light itself screamed."
  - line: 20
    type: narration
    text: "Mars burned to ash, and Tiamat shattered into storm and dust."
  - line: 21
    type: narration
    text: "Fragments of her body scattered through the dark, circling the newborn Earth like mourners in orbit."
  - line: 23
    type: narration
    text: "In the silent aftermath, an ethereal library drifted through the debris‚Äîits spires veiled in cloud, its runes dimly lit."
  - line: 24
    type: narration
    text: "The Akashic Records, carrying the memory of a world undone, turned slowly in the vacuum, waiting for a new planet to breathe."
  - line: 26
    type: narration
    text: "Three thousand five hundred years passed."
  - line: 27
    type: narration
    text: "Mars cooled into red desolation."
  - line: 28
    type: narration
    text: "Earth rose from ruin, green with possibility."
  - line: 29
    type: narration
    text: "Marduk returned, pulling behind it the fiery planet that had once followed in its shadow, a crimson omen of the next reckoning."
  - line: 32
    type: scene_header
    text: "---"
  - line: 34
    type: narration
    text: "Journal ‚Äì Keeper Vaelith, Observation 01"
  - line: 36
    type: narration
    text: "> The wound has closed, but the scar glows still."
  - line: 37
    type: narration
    text: "I watched the oceans fold themselves anew and the air shimmer as if embarrassed by survival."
  - line: 38
    type: narration
    text: "Tiamat‚Äôs heart beats now within another world, smaller, yet stubbornly alive."
  - line: 39
    type: narration
    text: "We drift above it, a library without a reader."
  - line: 40
    type: narration
    text: "I pray that when the next light comes, it finds us worthy of remembering."
