  - line: 57
    type: narration
    text: "Journal ‚Äî Keeper Lyaris, Entry #000-Vigil"
  - line: 59
    type: narration
    text: "> We have lingered in the interval between pulses for three thousand, four hundred and seventeen years."
  - line: 60
    type: narration
    text: "The planet hums again ‚Äî its new skin still wet with magma, its veins glowing with unspent vrill."
  - line: 61
    type: narration
    text: "Tomorrow we will attempt the old miracle ‚Äî send thought to walk once more."
  - line: 62
    type: narration
    text: "They will call themselves Neferati, though the name will change as tongues divide."
  - line: 63
    type: narration
    text: "If this is hubris, let the record show: creation always begins in loneliness."
